// ch11 §11.7: "extern without a "C" string declares a function with
// ordinary scpp linkage (not C ABI), whose implementation lives in a
// separate implementation unit or a separately-distributed `.scppo`
// object file." This module's bare, bodyless `extern int square(int x);`
// declaration has no implementation supplied anywhere in this test (a
// real implementation unit/`.scppo` pairing isn't modeled here), so it is
// never called -- this only confirms bare `extern` (distinct from
// `extern "C"`) is accepted as valid syntax for an exported, bodyless
// declaration, and that importing a module containing one compiles fine.
import mylib;

int main() {
    return 0;
}
